Well they gave it to me straight. Did the diagnosis for free as stated. Had a corrupted OS that wouldn't boot my computer. They wanted $149 to wipe and install a new OS on ssd. For the 30-45 day guarantee wanted an extra $199 to clean and disassemble the pc.

In total wanted $350. I ended up choosing not to take them up on their service but to leave a review on their cost estimate to inform others on their price. This may be standard rate but I didn't check other shops.

Anthony, the manager, and Andy the technician were very nice.<//text>

< review>
WARNING!!!
Do not go to this place, these people are either cheaters or unprofessionals (such level of unprofessionalism that they do not understand simplest things in computers). My computer suddenly stopped charging. I suspected that there is a problem either with a charger or some element where the charger is inserted (everything else was fine with my computer, it worked normally, except the fact that the battery finally died). I brought my computer to this company and after a day of investigation they said that the problem is not with the charger nor with the computer adapter, but some core modul is broken. And in order to fix it we need to order this replacement modul and the whole repairment process will cost more than a price of a new computer, around 500-800$ (!!!!). And it is not all. In order to recover the data from the broken computer we have to pay additionally 1200$. So around 2000$ all together!! However, if we buy a new computer from them, they will reduce the price of data recovering from 1200 to 900$. Fortunately, my husband understands something in computers, we did not do anything with them, just took the computer home. He just bought new adapter, tried to charge the "broken" computer and all of a sudden it worked! So now it is 100% charged and perfectly working. No need to restore data or repair it. If I would believe this people I would pay around 2000$. They probably get their profit such way, from people who do not understand themselves in computers and believe their words.</review>

< user>
117182932358856751699</user>
<user_name>Just AddWater</user_name>< Date>
1595989239292< /Date>
<Rate>1</Rate>< Text>
I realize this place has a really high rating but judging by the food I'm wondering if it's just heavy local favorite due to convenience. I happened to be passing through the area and thought I'd support a small private owned business vs some corporate money mill.
The girl helping us could not have been more awesome. Super friendly and upbeat.
She was the better part of the experience.
The food...
Not so awesome.
I ordered a 1/2 rice/chow mein combo with the fabled Lee's orange chicken, and potato chicken as the 2nd choice.
The fried rice was definitely "fried."
Super dry and tasted like burnt pan.
The noodles had a perfect texture, but tasted like they were tossed in well used frying oil.
It was hard to find much meat in the orange chicken through the thick batter, and the sauce was sweet as snow cone syrup.
The potato chicken had a delicious sauce, but the chicken portions were odds and ends of dark meat that looked like it was scrapped from another dish. The "potatoes" were crinkle cut fries that had become so soggy they barely held their shape.
I ate about a 1/3 of the food before completely tapping out.
If you're local and just need something immediately; completely understand.
But don't go outta your way for this one😬<//Text>

<user>108033000658731735410< /user><Name>Tom Lease< /Name><time>1432159001075< /time><rate>5</rate>< review>
Friend took me here today. He takes clients, co-workers, friends there and I am glad he took me. He has good taste so I knew it would be good since he is into quality fresh healthy food. So we went and he has what he always has...some meatball dish which I tried and it was very amazing. I had beef kabob. Since my wife is Persian and I have been to Iran three times I know all about kabobs. The meat was a perfectly cooked very tasty high quality beef along with a beautiful salad, excellent rice and middle eastern type bread.
The owner is a very nice guy. It is obvious from the food, service, decor and mood that this is a place that cares about offering great quality food with good service and great atmosphere. Take a chance on a new experience and go here and you will not be disappointed. Having a great meal inFoster City is something to be enjoyed and treasured. Support your small local business!</review>

< review>
Fast and friendly service. Ordered 5 drinks total. Didn’t take photos of all of them.

1. Strawberry matcha with ice cream - 1 out of 5, no matcha taste and can’t taste the ice cream. Won’t order again.

2. Mango sago with boba and salted cheese.  4 out of 5. While the drink taste great, there’s not much of the actual drink as it was filled with sago, boba and the a large piece of grapefruit topped with salted cheese. It doesn’t come in a large size. I would suggest asking them to put it in a bigger cup since you’re paying for all that extra. May order again if they are willing to put it in a bigger cup.

3. Oreo milk tea - 2 out of 5. Nothing special, can’t taste the Oreo. Meh...won’t order again.

4. Passion fruit green tea - 5 out of 5. Probably the best drink. Good amount of tea and taste great. Will order again.

5. Sticky rice milk tea - 3 out of 5. Odd combo but surprisingly good. The tea can be a bit stronger.  Might order again.<//review>

<text>Very excited ume tea(U & Me ;) ) shop recently opened in Milpitas Square!
Very cute store and super great taste milk tea store! !
Their fruit tea is made from fresh fruits!
Personally, I really liked the peach green tea(桃之夭夭), though white peach is out of season, so need to switch to other milk teas(mochi red bean milk tea is my new favorite :D ), and wait for fresh peach next year
Ordering is easy and convenient! There’s a Kiosk in the front, I can order by myself without contacting others, which is very needed and helpful during the special pandemic time!
Though there was one time we had a question, I went to the other side with ordering in person(with glass protection to keep distance), the front desk person was kind, and responsible, also very nice to give good suggestions to my friend(new customer) ! They would also nicely say “Thank You” when people picking up the orders!
Sometimes, during weekend, they were very busy, but they still try to see whether there’re people waiting, and do their best to avoid people waiting for too long, which I really appreciate and understand for their hard work, and trying to serve their best! As it’s not just in-person orders, but also online orders.

Now every time I go to Milpitas Square, will get some Ume tea 🍵 😋< /text><pictures>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMTsXMe4C_WbfUK310hkX9bYXErKp7U29wtf3Lw=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipM4SdTYY1MybCKCQdDcfovLQglgjH8ZFi-j2kvF=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipOjMMsvA-FWlsrPbx6Wgw6RGXS4eDeS1Upj-wsJ=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipOlHBoDdPb2VIicmveLEB6gkMoPKaUjSiJZY7AE=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]< /pictures><response>None< /response><gmap_id>0x808fc9f8fd43b137:0x11726a07fd178003<//gmap_id></record></dataset><record>

< text>
Since becoming pregnant i had the option of choosing between this place or Kaiser permante thru my husbands insurance which would kick in this January 2018...

However, I started attending here since November thru my current insurance and my experience with Janet Vadaparampil has been so pleasant. She’s very kind and attentive to my needs. She is always friendly and in a good mood. I enjoy chatting with her & im glad she’s available. Basically they want to make sure you’re guided correctly throughout your pregnancy.

I have been very happy that I decided to continue My OB services here, & I told my husband I didn’t want to chance it and end up with bad service somewhere else because at the end of the day, it all depends who you get- doesn’t matter how good of an insurance you have - it depends on the people that are taking care of you & I feel like I have been taken care of here.. don’t hesitate to sign up with them :)<//text>

< review>
$21 for the “exterior/wheel dressing/vacuum”wash. I’ve got a black SUV with leather interior and declined on the additional $20 wipe down interior service because there was only a little bit of sand on the seats from the beach and some crumbs in the cupholder. I collected all of my own trash in a plastic bag and threw it out before I left the car.

Got to the car at the finish and the car didn’t even looked vacuumed. The floor mats might have been shaken out and then put back in place (likely not vacuumed). There were suds dripping down the windows. The exterior looked like my eight-year-old child dried it off for me.

Manager offered to give me a free car wash on my next visit, but I rejected. I don’t have time to have another bad experience with so much competition out there and so many options.

Good people. Poor execution.</review>

< Review>
After mistakenly spilling some lotion on my new car's passenger seat, I came to Genie Car Wash in Vista for a shampoo. They did not remove the stain but they DID treat me rudely and damage my car.

After taking my car through the wash, an employee returned my car to me and said they were able to get the spot out, "no problem." My car was returned to me with a loose plastic sheet covering the seat. Regrettably, I did not check under the plastic sheet until I got home. I trusted them when they said the stain was gone and I did not even think to check for damage or anything like that... Big mistake. When I got home and removed the plastic, I unveiled a seat with the same stain plus threads popping up from the cushion.

I tried coming back the next day but it was Easter Sunday so they were closed. I work M-F and was not able to get back to Genie during their business hours until Saturday. In the meantime, I called and spoke with a woman who asked me to text her pictures of the damaged seat. I did that but did not hear back. I briefly talked with the manager by phone and agreed to meet him on Saturday.

On Saturday, the manager was rude to me when I showed him the damage and insisted it was my fault! He said that he shampoos many cars per day and no one else has had damage so I must have damaged the seat by having people sit in it with car keys in their pockets! Umm, this is a brand new car and no one sat in it between the time I had it cleaned and the time I brought it back to show him the damage.

After talking with the Subaru dealer who leased me the car, they referred me to a car interior specialist. That specialist said that it looked like an old machine was used and/or someone cleaned it too aggressively, and I will need to replace the seat covers.

I gave Genie's manager the opportunity to make things right, asking him to at least refund me the $50 I spent on the wash plus $150, which is the minimum it will cost for me to have the Subaru professional steam clean the seat. In response, the manager tried to give me coupons for more washes! Obviously, I am not going to risk a wash here ever again. He finally agreed to refund me $50 when I mentioned that I saw reviews on Yelp and Google and know I am not the only one who has suffered damages at his business.

I hope I have saved at least one person from a terrible experience here. :(< /Review>

<user_id>116493242431796076610<//user_id><pics>None< /pics><date>1594676258954< /date><Gmap_id>0x80dc74dd06ed30c3:0x8653005d56bd8220</Gmap_id>< Text>
I have 2 issues with my experience at Genie Car Wash.

#1: the actual car detailing was not very good. I paid for the Complete package, everything, for $350. That's a lot of money for me, but I wanted to get the family car as clean as possible.
When I came back to pick up the car, 2/4 wheels hadn't been cleaned. There was tree sap still on 1 of the moonroof windows. Several marks on the bumper and passenger door came right off with my finger, and obviously those areas didn't get the clay bar treatment.
4/7 seats still had crumbs/dust in the folds of the upholstery, the space on the floor between the front passengers feet hadn't been wiped down, I emptied the center console before bringing it in and they didn't vacuum in there. 1 cupholder still had dust and grunge in it, not touched at all.

#2 issue: they didn't call me when it was ready for pickup. They said it could be up to 3 hours, I waited 3 hours and then called in to be told it was already ready for pickup. When I got there and found all these issues, I had to wait while they worked on them.

For that much money and time, I don't think I should expect to be the QC person for the job. Whatever their process is for making sure the work is done, it is inadequate.

The actual parts the did get clean look great. The tires and 2/4 wheels were sharp! The plastics all throughout the interior were very clean and conditioned, the windshield was super-clean. The carpets were shampooed and honestly haven't been this clean in years. Even the roof rack was clean and polished.

Obviously they can do good work. They just weren't consistent about it. Not recommended.< /Text>

< Review>
We needed a storage unit asap and the staff at US Storage was absolutely helpful. We came in for a quote and got the best rate. Matthew helped us look at 3 units in person on a Saturday and answered all our questions. The facility is clean and secure. We secured our unit the following Monday and Yvette and Phil helped get us set up and explained all the rental details, monthly payments and gate access. Staff is very friendly and compassionate and I would definitely recommended this facility especially in a time crunch.</Review>

<userid>116528117830833143869<//userid>< review>
I have rented storage space from a handful of companies over the years. Most places are all about the same . . . modest to modern offices, and rental spaces that consist of a metal door and ceiling, and three walls of drywall, decorated with plywood patches covering damaged drywall. They all charge close to the same rates for about the same services.

So I was skeptical when my realtor highly recommended US Storage on Foster Road in Norwalk, just because she had nothing but the highest praise for this location, where she stores her own personal stuff. If it weren't for the fact that she is also a dear friend, I would have suspected she was recommending it for a kickback.

The rent for the Public Storage room I had was going up 20% after only three months, despite the fact they had NOT indicated what I'd been paying was an introductory rate. So I knew I had to get out of there fast, and researched my friend's recommendation of US Storage online, and arranged to go in to rent a unit. I expected to see what I've always seen at storage places, so I was absolutely floored when I got there, and saw that it was everything my friend had said . . .

First impression was amazing! This place is huge, with the buildings facing the street decorated to look like pleasant housing or office parks so it doesn't look like an unsightly industrial block to mar the look of the neighborhood. Their office is modern and pleasant, and I was immediately greeted by the managers, Yvette and Filbert, who were very friendly, efficient, accommodating and informative. They did everything they could to make the transition easier, including the FREE use of their moving truck for the day!

Filbert took me out to the unit in a golf cart, and I could see their location is huge! Over 1,000 units! The area was neat and clean, and solar panels provide their electricity needs. Everything about the place told me it was well~planned and executed, corporate~run, not a franchise, and everything run to corporate standards!

THE BEST PART was seeing the unit itself! No pockmarked drywall with plywood decor! Wall to wall, floor to ceiling was clean corrugated metal walls, to keep the contents safe from being pilfered through through units! I loved that the units have ALARMS with a clever means of activation, and the doors have a locking system like nothing I've seen before, absolutely unbreakable. The unit looked brand new and well~sealed against pests.

All of this, and their prices are absolutely competitive with other companies! Now I understand my friend's excitement! Just like I was floored by my friend's recommendation, which seemed just impossible or at the very least, very exaggerated, now YOU're reading MY review and probably thinking the same thing. I assure you, prior to my friend's recommendation, I'd had NO knowledge of or affiliation with US Storage ~ Foster, and there is no monetary benefit for writing this review. I just wish I'd found them years ago, if there is anything I can do to send customers their way, AND also help YOU by recommending a great storage facility, I'm happy to do it! Life has enough complications, more things in life need to be this easy and worry~free!

:-) Have a lovely day!</review>
